metadata.title: Piper Aerostar
aws::graph::propositions: # Piper Aerostar Variants
Piper Aerostar Model 320 was the first prototype.
Piper Aerostar Model 320 was powered by two 160 hp (120 kW) Lycoming IO-320 engines.
Piper Aerostar Model 360 was a modification of the first prototype.
Piper Aerostar Model 360 had two 180 hp (130 kW) Lycoming IO-360 engines.
Piper Aerostar Model 360 featured a redesigned empennage.
Piper Aerostar Model 400 was a modification of the first prototype.
Piper Aerostar Model 400 had two 200 hp (150 kW) IO-360 engines.
Piper Aerostar Model 400 was type certified.
Piper Aerostar Model 400 did not enter production.
Piper Aerostar Model 500 was a projected version with 250 hp (190 kW) fuel injected engines.
Piper Aerostar Model 500 was designed to be non-pressurized.
Piper Aerostar Model 500 was never built.
Piper Aerostar Model 500P was a projected version with 250 hp (190 kW) fuel injected engines.
Piper Aerostar Model 500P was designed to be pressurized.
Piper Aerostar Model 500P was never built.
Piper Aerostar 600 was later designated as PA-60-600.
Piper Aerostar 600 was the initial production model.
Piper Aerostar 600 had two 290 hp (220 kW) Lycoming IO-540-K engines.
282 Piper Aerostar 600 aircraft were produced under four different company names.
Piper Aerostar 600A was a Model 600 with some minor detail changes.
Piper Aerostar 600A had improved engines compared to Model 600.

text:
## Variants
Model 320
First prototype, powered by two 160 hp (120 kW) Lycoming IO-320 engines
Model 360
Modification of first prototype with two 180 hp (130 kW) Lycoming IO-360 engines and a redesigned empennage
Model 400
Modification of first prototype with two 200 hp (150 kW) IO-360 engines; type certified, but did not enter production
Model 500/500P
Projected versions with 250 hp (190 kW) fuel injected engines, to be non-pressurized and pressurized respectively; none built
600 (later PA-60-600)
Initial production model with two 290 hp (220 kW) Lycoming IO-540-K engines, 282 produced under four different company names
600A
Model 600 with some minor detail changes and improved engines,
